#. +> trunk5
#: ../../effects_and_filters/video_effects/motion/freeze.rst:48
msgid "This effect causes the video to freeze. By default, the clip will be frozen for its entire length when the effect is added to the clip. To change this, check either the :guilabel:`Freeze Before` or :guilabel:`Freeze After` option and move the :guilabel:`Freeze at` slider to the time where you want the freeze to start or end. The audio in the video plays for the entire length, i.e. the **Freeze** effect does *not* affect the audio."
msgstr ""

